Wash and dry produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from
greens. Dice @tomato{1} into ¼-inch pieces. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high
heat. Add scallion whites; cook, stirring occasionally, until
lightly browned and fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @ground beef{10%oz}, @Mexican spice blend{1%tbsp}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}.
Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until beef is
browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} more.

In the last minute of cooking, stir in @green salsa{7.06%oz}.

> Rinse shrimp under cold water; pat dry with paper towels. Swap in shrimp (no need to break up into pieces!) or beef for turkey.

While beef cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomato,
scallion greens, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, and a squeeze of
lemon juice (big squeeze for 4 servings). Season with
salt and pepper.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until
warm and pliable, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with spicy beef.
Top with pico de gallo and drizzle with @crema{3%tbsp}. Serve
tacos with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Ground beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.